properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 3:17AM CST until January 14 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...ACCUMULATING SNOW EXPECTED THIS EVENING THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING...

.A potent, but fast-moving, system will pass through the region
this evening through Tuesday morning, which will bring some
widespread accumulating snow to the Northland. The heaviest snow
is anticipated to fall along the North Shore tonight, thanks to
lake enhanced snowfall due to persistent southerly winds. Some
freezing drizzle may mix in at times during the early morning
hours Tuesday, but snow will be the primary threat.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations of
3 to 5 inches and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Southern Cook County. This includes the Tribal Lands
of the Grand Portage Reservation.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 9 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Tuesday morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 9 AM CST TUESDAY
